# Add Tabs
## Vertical Tabs
To make a multi stepped layout, we offer a tabbed layout which can be used to create a tabular structure. From the [story book example](https://opensource.adobe.com/aem-forms-af-runtime/storybook/?path=/story/adaptive-form-layouts-tabs--vertical), we can notice wrapping a Form in a Panel with `":type" : "custom:vertical-tab"` can create the following structure. From the documentation a two step form can be creating using the following JSON

```json
{
  "items": [
    {
      ":type": "custom:vertical-tab",
      "name": "tabs",
      ...
      "items": [
        {
          "name": "textInput",
          ...
          "fieldType": "text-input"
        },
        {
          "name": "item3",
          ...
          "fieldType": "panel",
          "items": [
            {
              "name": "firstName",
              ...
              "fieldType": "text-input"
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}
```

## Add tabs in our form

To add tabs in our login form as per the requirement we need to make modification to our json.

> You can directly copy the contents of the JSON Document to see the tabs in your form [here](https://raw.githubusercontent.com/adobe/aem-forms-af-runtime/lab2/ui.frontend.react.forms.af/examples/multistep/loan-form-tabs.form.json). Just ensure you keep the `action` property present in the original json downloaded from AEM

1. Create a Panel Wizard as the first child of the Form element

```json
{
    "name": "wizard",
    "label": {
        "value": "Welcome"
    },
    ":type": "custom:vertical-tab",
    "items" : []
}
```

2. Inside the newly created Panel add two Panels : `step1` and `step2`

```json
{
    "name": "wizard",
    "label": {
        "value": "Welcome"
    },
    ":type": "custom:vertical-tab",
    "items" : [{
        "name" : "step1",
        "fieldType" : "panel",
        "label": {
            "value": "Identify Yourself"
        },
        "items": []
    },
    {
        "name" : "step2",
        "fieldType" : "panel",
        "label": {
            "value": "Verify OTP"
        },
        "items": []
    }
    ]
}
```

3. In the items of `step1` panel move the fields `mobileNumber`, `creditCardEndingNumber`, `viewEligibilityButton`. After this step the step1 panel would have the following json

```json
{
        "name" : "step1",
        "fieldType" : "panel",
        "label": {
            "value": "Identify Yourself"
        },
        "items": [
        {
            "name": "mobileNumber",
            "fieldType": "text-input",
            "type": "string",
            "required": true,
            "description": "You do not need to add +91 - Share your 10 digit mobile number.\n We will be sending you an OTP to this number have it handy.",
            "label": {
                "value": "Please share your registered mobile number"
            }
        },
        {
            "name": "creditCardEndingNumber",
            "fieldType": "text-input",
            "type": "string",
            "required": true,
            "description": "We will need your credit card number to check your eligibility",
            "label": {
                "value": "Share last 4 digits of your credit card number"
            }
        },
        {
            "name": "viewEligibilityButton",
            "fieldType": "button",
            "label": {
                "value": "View Loan Eligibility 1"
            }
        }]
    }
```

4. Similarly in the `step2` panel add the fields `identifyOtpValue` and `viewEligibilityConfirmButton`.
5. Add the remaining two panels from the form `loanDetails` and `acountDetails` as siblings of `step1` and `step2`

After completing the steps, your file should look exactly like the JSON Document present [here](https://raw.githubusercontent.com/adobe/aem-forms-af-runtime/lab2/ui.frontend.react.forms.af/examples/multistep/loan-form-tabs.form.json) and look like the image below

> Note that an extra `action` property would be present in the form downloaded from AEM

![Form with Tabs](/assets/tutorial/lab2/loan-form-steps.png)
